CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, page 18, reads: "5. The Bell Telephone Company installed live telephones in their booth. Hosteses [sic] Doris Thomas and Barbara Thompson are shown here with representatives, Rodger [sic] Drake, Charles Jackson, Norman Back and Bob Bayer."
TitMainTitle: Doris Thomas and Barbara Thompson with representatives possibly including Roger Drake, Charles Jackson, Norman Back, or Bob Bayer, gathered in Bell Telephone Company booth in Syria Mosque for the 1956 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
